1 AN ACT concerning motor vehicles; relating to vehicle registrations;
2 modifying the threshold limit for allowing quarterly payments of
3 certain truck and truck tractor annual vehicle registration fees;
4 eliminating the two-quarter grace period for truck or truck tractor
5 owners that have delinquent quarterly payments before certain penalties
6 apply; {extending from 10 to 30 days when payments would be
7 considered delinquent;} amending K.S.A. 8-143a and repealing the
8 existing section.
9
10 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
11 Section 1. K.S.A. 8-143a is hereby amended to read as follows: 8-
12 143a. (a) The provisions of this section shall not apply to vehicles
13 registered on an apportioned basis as part of a fleet under the provisions of
14 K.S.A. 8-1,101 to through 8-1,123, inclusive, and amendments thereto, or
15 any agreement made by the director of vehicles, and. The payment of
16 registration fees on a quarterly basis on such vehicles shall be in
17 accordance with K.S.A. 8-1,115, and amendments thereto.
18 (b) A resident owner of any truck or truck tractor, holding a
19 negotiable Kansas title, whether individual, partnership or Kansas
20 corporation, may at such owner's election, made at the time the annual
21 registration fee on such truck or truck tractor is payable, pay such annual
22 registration fee if it such fee exceeds $100 $300, in equal quarterly
23 installments,. The first of which such quarterly payments shall be payable
24 at the time of such application but not later than the last day of February in
25 each year, and for each ensuing quarter thereafter shall be payable
26 respectively on the first day of April, July and October. The applicant
27 shall, at the time of registration, present such applicant's negotiable Kansas
28 title to the county treasurer, who shall send it, along with the application
29 for registration, to the division of vehicles. The division of vehicles shall
30 retain the title until all quarterly payments are paid in full, at which time
31 the title shall be returned to the owner of the vehicle to which the title was
32 issued.
33 (c) The provisions of the preceding paragraph subsection (b) shall not
34 in any manner be construed to affect or reduce the amount of annual
35 registration fee due for any truck or truck tractor subject to registration on

