1 January 1, and for which the owner shall be liable, but relate only to an
2 alternate method of payment of the amount of fees due and affixed as of
3 January 1 of each year. If any owner shall default in the payment of any
4 quarterly installment payment when the same is payable, the right to
5 operate such vehicle on the highways of this state shall terminate and it
6 shall be unlawful to operate such vehicle on the highways of this state until
7 the delinquent quarterly installment payment plus any penalty, shall have
8 been paid in full.
9 (d) (1) If any owner shall fail to pay any two quarterly payment
10 installments during any one registration year on any truck or truck tractor
11 registered hereunder, on or before the day the same are due and payable,
12 such owner thereafter may be denied the privilege of the payment of
13 annual registration fees on a quarterly basis on any vehicle. If a quarterly
14 installment payment shall be delinquent more than 10 {30} days beyond
15 the due date of such quarterly installment, except for any case where it is
16 determined by the director of vehicles that such delinquency is not due to
17 negligence or intentional disregard of the provisions of this section, then
18 the entire balance of the annual registration fee, including the delinquent
19 quarterly installment, plus a penalty in a sum equal to 10% of the annual
20 registration fee, shall become due and payable; and. Any such owner so
21 delinquent may thereafter be denied the privilege of the payment of annual
22 registration fees on any vehicle on a quarterly basis. All such fees and
23 penalties remaining unpaid shall constitute a debt due the state, which may
24 be collected from the person owing the same such unpaid fees and
25 penalties by suit or otherwise. All such fees and any penalties remaining
26 unpaid after the same such fees and any penalties are due and payable and
27 any penalties shall constitute a first and prior lien in favor of the state upon
28 the truck or truck tractor registered hereunder under this section, and all
29 other real and personal property of the owner located within the state in the
30 amount such fees and penalties remain unpaid. Each lien shall attach at the
31 time such unpaid fees and penalties accrue and shall be paramount to all
32 prior liens or encumbrances of any character and to the rights of any
33 holder of the legal title in or to any such truck or truck tractor.
34 (2) When a quarterly installment is delinquent more than 10 {30} days
35 beyond the due date, upon default of such installment payment, the county
36 treasurer shall promptly file a notice of lien in the office of the register of
37 deeds of the county where the registration fee is payable, and in any other
38 county in which such owner has any property. A copy of such notice of
39 lien shall be mailed to the division of vehicles, and the owner so
40 delinquent, and the sheriff of any county in which such notice of lien is
41 filed. Such notice of lien shall set forth the name and address of the owner,
42 the amount of fees and penalties payable and unpaid, and the description
43 of the vehicle or vehicles to which applicable to such notice of lien. It shall

