1 be the duty of each register of deeds in this state to index and file
2 immediately all such notices of lien in the manner provided in cases of
3 financing statements and no fee shall be charged for filing and indexing.
4 (3) The county treasurer shall issue a release of lien upon payment of
5 all fees and penalties payable by such owner and such person may file the
6 same with the register of deeds of any county in which such notice of lien
7 has been filed. The county treasurer shall mail a copy of the release of lien
8 to the division, and to the sheriff of any county where said such notice of
9 lien has been filed.
10 (4) If a quarterly installment payment shall be delinquent more than
11 10 {30} days beyond the due date of such quarterly installment, the
12 division, shall promptly on such default and the filing of the notice of lien
13 issue a tax warrant to the sheriff of any county in which such notice of lien
14 has been filed and may thereafter issue further warrants as may be
15 necessary, and. Such sheriff shall seize and hold all personal property
16 subject thereto to such lien and proceed to advertise and sell the same such
17 property or so much thereof as may be necessary, to satisfy the state's lien,
18 together with all expense of selling at public sale for cash, upon such
19 notice as is provided by law in the case of a security agreement sale.
20 (5) Any surplus of the proceeds of such sale, after paying to the
21 county treasurer, the amount of the state's lien, and the cost of the officer
22 in giving notice of and executing said such warrant computed to the same
23 extent as in judicial sales on execution, and of securing and preserving the
24 property pending such sale, shall be delivered to the person lawfully
25 entitled thereto to such surplus amount. In the event that any truck or truck
26 tractor for which the annual registration fee is being paid quarterly shall be
27 sold or otherwise disposed of, the entire balance remaining unpaid on such
28 annual registration fee shall become immediately due and payable.
29 (6) No certificate of title shall be assigned or transferred or new
30 certificate of title be issued for such vehicle until all the registration fees
31 and penalties are paid in full. In the event such vehicle shall be
32 repossessed by the enforcement of a lien or security interest on the same
33 such vehicle, during any quarterly period for which the registration fees
34 have not been paid, the person repossessing such vehicle or the person
35 purchasing such vehicle at a repossession sale, may acquire a new
36 certificate of title upon the payment of a fee equal to 1/ of the annual
