2 not affect or reduce the original amount of the annual registration fee or
3 any quarterly installment payment, for which such owner was originally
4 liable.
5 (e) The division of vehicles may call to its aid the state highway
6 patrol or any peace officer or any duly appointed representative of the
7 department to enforce the provisions of this section within their respective
8 jurisdiction and it shall be the duty of such officers to do so. The remedies
9 for enforcement and collection provided in this section are cumulative and
10 the use of one shall not be deemed to be a waiver of the right to use any
11 other.
12 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 8-143a is hereby repealed.
13 Sec. 3. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
14 publication in the statute book.

